item.title: Problems with others connecting to my server Ip/Ports [Pictues]
item.dc:creator: @runefreak10 runefreak10
item.description:
@runefreak10 wrote:

192.168.1.2 should be 192.168.1.101 (Game Port 2 is not needed, as the protocol for RSPS is TCP, not UDP.)

Turn your firewall off or make an exception for the port 43594.

Go to http://whatismyip.com/ and try logging in with the IP it gives you there. If you can log in with that IP, then others will be able to log into your server.

If it still doesn’t work, post here. I have another solution.

Read full topic

item.dc:creator: @Xx_R_A_G_3_R Xx R A G 3 R
item.description:
@Xx_R_A_G_3_R wrote:

Change it to “192.168.1.254”
Open up your firewall and allow an exception for port 43594 TCP.
Go to canyouseeme.org and see if your port 43594 is open. Also, give it a little time after you make these changes, it doesn’t always instantly open up the port. Atleast, it didn’t for me. Be patient, post back if it doesn’t work.
